6. The elastomer composite material of claim 1 wherein the polysiloxane particles are selected from the product of crosslinked siloxanes comprising: 
a) at least one vinyl addition curable poly-functional polydi(C1-8 alkyl)siloxane, said siloxane polymer comprising at least two reactive functional units selected from the group consisting of monofunctional, difunctional, trifunctional and tetrafunctional siloxane units; 
b) at least one condensation curable polyfunctional polydi(C1-8 alkyl)siloxane, said siloxane polymer comprising at least two reactive functional units selected from the group consisting of monofunctional, difunctional, trifunctional and tetrafunctional siloxane units; 
c) at least one peroxide curable polyfunctional polydi(C1-8 alkyl)siloxane, said siloxane polymer comprising at least two reactive functional units selected from the group consisting of monofunctional, difunctional, trifunctional and tetrafunctional siloxane units; and combinations of a), b), and c).

13. The elastomer composite material of claim 1 comprising: 
3-300 parts of cured silicone elastomer particles; 
0.2 to 12 parts of a fluorocarbon crosslinking agent; 
0-10 parts of an optional fluorocarbon-curing accelerator; 
and 0-25 parts of an optional acid acceptor filler; 
all based on 100 parts of a fluorocarbon elastomer.

20. A method of making a coating for an imaging member comprising: 
a) preparing a polymeric composition according to claim 1 or 13; 
b) adding a fluorocarbon curing agent; 
c) coating the article with the polymeric composition; and 
d) curing the coating.
